The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sunday, May 15, 2005 

 Security expert in custody

 Durgapur, May 14: Coke Oven police arrested Anjan Chowdhury, a former regional director of a Mumbai-based private security agency, last night for misappropriating Rs 1.4 crore from the firm, reports our correspondent.

 Another accused, Arup Chatterjee, is absconding. Chatterjee, who used to oversee work at the Durgapur office, 200 km from Calcutta, has also been charged with giving youths false assurances of jobs in exchange for money.

 Chowdhury, who was arrested from his Selimpur Road residence in Calcutta, was produced before the Durgapur subdivisional judicial magistrate and remanded in police custody for three days.




